<h1>User Manual</h1>
<p>Welcome to the User page. Here you can learn about how the site runs and how to use it.</p>

<h3>Introduction</h2>
<p>
    This user manual describes how to use the YMCA Project website.  You can use this site under three different levels, as a user, 
    a staff or an admin. As a user you can either be a member or a nonmember of the YMCA, which you can sign up for on the site. 
    As a member you have access to cheaper programs. As a user you can choose to become a member, login, view programs to register for 
    or view programs that you are registered for, register for programs, search for programs, and cancel your registration. Staff and admin 
    have a separate login that is associated with their membership status and allows for them to interact with the site as a member. For staff, 
    you can login, add, edit, or cancel programs. For admin, you can login, add, edit, or cancel/delete programs, staff members, or YMCA members. 
    This site is connected to a database that holds all of the user, staff, admin, and program information. 
</p>
<hr>

<h2>Requirements</h2>
<p>
    Must have a web browser and web access. You can access this site via any machine with these capabilities. 
</p>
<hr>

<h2>Getting Started</h2>
<p>
    In order to get started you first need to load up the webpage. On the homepage shown a user can: 
    <ul>
        <li>Login in order to access the tools associated to their account</li>
        <ul>
            <li><i> Members/Non Members click 'User Login' button to log in</i></li>
            <li><i>Staff/Admin click 'Staff Login' button to log in</i></li>
        </ul>
        <li>Check out programs that are currently being offered</li>
        <li>Choose to sign up as a member </li>
        <li>Check out this user manual </li>
    </ul>
</p>
